feed.title: Murray Sunset Np North Flora North Of Sturt Hwy

entry.title: Atriplex vesicaria subsp. macrocystidia
entry.content: On roadside. Probably Atriplex lindleyi lindleyi at bottom of pic.

entry.title: Zygophyllum apiculatum
entry.content: Five petals and largeish, roundish leaves are a good feature combination for ID. Flowering on roadside, probably taking advantage of road verge water run-off. Unusual flowering time according to the books.

entry.title: Teucrium racemosum s.s., Theclinesthes serpentata serpentata
Minuria denticulata
entry.content: Flowering on roadside. Second pic shows it growing in among Teucrium racemosum.

entry.title: Goodenia heteromera
entry.content: Spreading Stolons. Seen at two spots on the Lake Wallawalla circuit.

entry.title: Calotis scapigera
entry.content: Pretty much scabrous, forming large mats as it spreads by stolons. Next to an arm off the Murray (in flood) that leads to Lake Wallawalla. Plants within 10m of the river bank.
